	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p>To <addressee>Mr. Zalme Rehine</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">care of <persName>Miss Judah Bloch</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName></p>
				<p>Single</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> <date>April 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Nisan 23rd 5596</date>.</p>
				<p>Dear Uncle</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I received your note the day before the <sic>holydays</sic>&#44; and would have<lb/> answered it immediately&#44; but that I had nothing to write&#44; and I would rather wait<lb/> till something was settled with regard to myself&#59; but again today there was no<lb/> meeting of the congregation and consequently nothing is known or determined<lb/> with respect to my future stay here.  There is no probability that there will be<lb/> any meeting before the next <sic>holydays</sic>&#44; and of course I must be kept in doubt till<lb/> then.  I hardly know what to make of the people&#44; they ought to know that it must be<lb/> very unpleasant to be kept in suspense&#44; still they seem to care little or nothing<lb/> about the whole matter&#44; and of course I must and do feel very unpleasantly&#44;<lb/> especially as daily some little things occur to make things very uncomfortable.<lb/>  Especially this day week I thought it my duty to speak to the people about the<lb/> many wrong things I see every day&#59; and you never saw or hear such an outcry as<lb/> there was made about it&#59; every one had something to say and some of the ladies<lb/> warmly approved&#44; but many of the men condemned me&#44; and could have eaten me up.  I<lb/> am really tired of having to defend myself constantly from one charged or the<lb/> other which is always made and really it appears that my congregation are never<lb/> tired of worrying me&#8212;when you come here which I hope will be very soon&#44; I shall<lb/> show you my sermon&#44; and tell you perhaps some other things as I wish to hear your<lb/> advise too in my future movements&#59; for I do not like to take my step without<lb/> hearing your opinion first.&#8212;Subscription to my book does not seem to be thought of<lb/> at least I hear nothing about it.  Perhaps after a while it may do&#44; but people<lb/> feel very indifferent about me and my doing.</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I hear that <persName>Zipporeh Seixas</persName> is engaged to her cousin <persName>Ben</persName> Son of <persName>Sol<lb/> Seixas</persName>&#59; a son of <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName> to a daughter of <persName>Hendricks</persName> and a daughter of the former<lb/> to a son of the latter&#59; besides report speaks of the engagement of <persName>Jeanette Ann</persName><lb/> &#38; <persName>Rebecca Kursheedt</persName> besides that <add>&#63;</add> is positively to be married to a <add>&#63;</add><lb/> <persName>Hannah Duke</persName> of <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I believe from enquiries made that my sister has received your<lb/> but I have not yet heard direct from her.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have also delivered another address on the Messiah subject not yet<lb/> complete.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am so nervous and my hand shakes so much that I can hardly write&#44; so<lb/> please to excuse the bad appearance of this note&#44; which I would not have sent in my<lb/> present frame of mind if I did not think my duty to delay writing no longer.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Give my love to aunt and all the family and believe me <sic>tobe</sic></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Your obt. Nephew&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author"><sic>Issac Lesser</sic></persName>.</p>
		</body>
